 <br><a href="https://karlsayle.github.io?query=tag:climate_temperate" class="tag" target="_blank" rel="noopener">#climate_temperate</a> <a href="https://karlsayle.github.io?query=tag:danger-level_safe" class="tag" target="_blank" rel="noopener">#danger-level_safe</a> <a href="https://karlsayle.github.io?query=tag:alignment_lawful_neutral" class="tag" target="_blank" rel="noopener">#alignment_lawful_neutral</a><br><br>Steading: Large city<br><br>Region: <a data-href="Királynők" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/places/regions/királynők.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">Királynők</a><br><br>
<br>Source: The Circle City
<br>Common: Körvá
<br>Elven: Dynas Gyll
<br>Dwarven: 
<br>Orcish: 
<br><br>
<br>Predominately <a data-href="Human" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/Human" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">Human</a> but other non-magical races visit often for trade
<br><br>
<br>Körvá gets its name from its impressive circular outer wall - directly translating to 'The Circle City'
<br>The Folyó (river) Kör winds its way through the city from the North East to the Southern border
<br>Even though magic was forbidden and looked down upon as cheap tricks and a way of cheating a good day's work, the people of Körvá still knew the value of knowledge, and the value of understanding the magical races (‘Know your foe’) and so had a vast resource of books and scripture curated by their most respected sages over the period of the city's history.&nbsp;
<br>Despite the people's outlook on magic, the restricted area has a sizeable collection of books on the arcane and the occult which is restricted to all but the highest ranking military officials, sages, politicians and members of the royal family.
<br>The people of Körvá pride themselves on being a democratic and fair society where men and women are seen as equals.
<br>Körvá has a strong military force that protects their people and interests both domestically and abroad. It is governed primarily by parliament but also answers to the royal family as has been the city's tradition for centuries.
<br>The people have a strong work ethic - a hard day's work is a hard day's work regardless of whether you are a knight or a farmer, they are all equally respected.&nbsp;
]]></description><link>https://karlsayle.github.io/places/steadings/körvá.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">Places/Steadings/Körvá.md</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Karl Sayle]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 26 Feb 2024 22:09:10 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Welcome]]></title><description><![CDATA[ 
